## ğŸŒŸ Quick Commands Reference

```bash
# Explore filesystem
ls -la /                    # List root directory
tree -L 1 /                 # Tree view (1 level)
du -sh /*                   # Size of top-level directories

# Find large directories
du -sh /* | sort -rh | head -10

# Check disk usage
df -h                       # All mounted filesystems
df -h /home                 # Specific mount point

# View filesystem hierarchy manual
man hier

# Check filesystem type
df -T

# Find files in specific directory
find /etc -name "*.conf"
find /var/log -name "*.log" -mtime -7

# Monitor directory changes
watch -n 1 'ls -lh /var/log'
```

